description.narrative: ROSA Evaluation prioritized country office support to increase the number of completed evaluations. These rose from 10 [2018] to 18 [2019] and 2020 targets are ambitious too. More global financial support, more internal quality assurance, and management support from the RO and COs explain the increase. A Regional Evaluation Strategy and a regional action plan to contextualize UNICEF's Evaluation Policy are in place. ROSA and its counterpart at CO are actively engaged in evidence generation activities as part of COVID response. Cooperation with HQ on capacity building is addressing skills development, evaluation services, and methods development. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/08/2020
